sentences.sContent: I could just make out a tall, pale, shadowy figure tramping through the undergrowth.
sentences.sCn: 我只能看出一个高高的、苍白的、朦胧的人影穿行在矮灌木丛中。

sentences.sContent: She thought she heard a name. She couldn't make it out, though.
sentences.sCn: 她以为自己听到了一个名字，但听不清楚。

synos.tran: 理解；辨认出；说明；填写；设法应付

trans.tranOther: If you make something out, you manage with difficulty to see or hear it
